Detailed Description

Value::String

	Usage:  $s = String("pole");
		ANS($s->cmp(typeMatch => Complex("4+i")));
		    # compare to response 'pole', don't complain about complex number responses.
		compareOptions and default values:
		  showTypeWarnings => 1,
		  showEqualErrors  => 1,
		  ignoreStrings    => 1   # don't complain about string-valued responses
		  typeMatch        => 'ValueReal'
	Initial and final spaces are ignored when comparing strings.

sub compare {
  my ($l,$r,$flag) = @_;
  my $sgn = ($flag ? -1: 1);
  $r = $l->promote($r);
  return 0 if !$r->classMatch('Real') && $l->{isNegative} == $r->{isNegative};
  return ($l->{isNegative}? -$sgn: $sgn);
}

sub neg {
  my $self = shift;
  my $neg = $self->Package("Infinity")->new($self->context);
  $neg->{isNegative} = !$self->{isNegative};
  $neg->{data}[0] = '-'.$neg->{data}[0] if $neg->{isNegative};
  return $neg;
}

# Number of lines of code in new: 10
sub new {
  my $self = shift; my $class = ref($self) || $self;
  my $context = (Value::isContext($_[0]) ? shift : $self->context);
  Value::Error("Infinity should have no parameters") if scalar(@_);
  bless {
    data => [$self->getFlag('infiniteWord')],
    isInfinite => 1, isNegative => 0,
    context => $context,
  }, $class;
}

public method Value::Infinity::promote (  )

# Number of lines of code in promote: 9
sub promote {
  my $self = shift; my $class = ref($self) || $self;
  my $context = (Value::isContext($_[0]) ? shift : $self->context);
  my $x = (scalar(@_) ? shift : $self); $x = [$x,@_] if scalar(@_) > 0;
  $x = Value::makeValue($x,context=>$context);
  return $x->inContext($context)
    if ref($x) eq $class || ref($x) eq $pkg || Value::isReal($x);
  Value::Error("Can't convert %s to %s",Value::showClass($x),$self->showClass);
}

sub typeMatch {
  my $self = shift; my $other = shift; my $ans = shift;
  return 1 unless ref($other);
  return 0 if Value::isFormula($other);
  return 1 if $other->type eq 'Number';
  $self->type eq $other->type;
}
